        "number": 71,
        "repo": "sonic-ztp",
        "comment_at": "2026-02-13T01:25:43Z",
        "comment_author": "Ryangwaite",
        "comment_body": "I have tested this on 72ede5c6cd1a69de4c8997eaa1ffa5d0e64269fd and these are the logs i see in `/var/log/ztp.log` after booting:\r\n```\r\n2026 Feb 13 00:27:03.339208 sonic INFO sonic-ztp[13184]: ZTP service started.\r\n2026 Feb 13 00:27:03.352529 sonic INFO sonic-ztp[13184]: minigraph.xml found, skipping ZTP discovery.\r\n2026 Feb 13 00:27:03.352657 sonic INFO sonic-ztp[13184]: Configuration file '/etc/sonic/config_db.json' detected. Shutting down ZTP service.\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt is almost correct but that last log line is misleading. This device did not have a `/etc/sonic/config_db.json` only a `/etc/sonic/minigraph.xml` and it's the minigraph file that was detected.\r\n\r\n"
    },
    {
        "number": 71,
        "repo": "sonic-ztp",
        "comment_at": "2026-02-13T18:04:36Z",
        "comment_author": "mssonicbld",
        "comment_body": "/azp run"
    },
    {
        "number": 71,
        "repo": "sonic-ztp",
        "comment_at": "2026-02-13T18:04:45Z",
        "comment_author": "azure-pipelines",
        "comment_body": "<samp>\nAzure Pipelines successfully started running 1 pipeline(s).<br>\r\n\n</samp>"
    },
    {
        "number": 71,
        "repo": "sonic-ztp",
        "comment_at": "2026-02-13T18:06:07Z",
        "comment_author": "yxieca",
        "comment_body": "Thanks for testing @Ryangwaite! Good catch on the misleading log message.\n\nFixed in ab3497f \u2014 the MANUAL_CONFIG shutdown log now correctly reports which file triggered the skip:\n- minigraph.xml present \u2192 logs \"Configuration file /etc/sonic/minigraph.xml detected\"\n- config_db.json present \u2192 logs \"Configuration file /etc/sonic/config_db.json detected\"\n- Warm boot / other \u2192 logs \"Manual configuration detected\"\r\n"
    },
    {
        "number": 71,
        "repo": "sonic-ztp",
        "comment_at": "2026-02-16T07:22:07Z",
        "comment_author": "mssonicbld",
        "comment_body": "/azp run"
    },
    {
        "number": 71,
        "repo": "sonic-ztp",
        "comment_at": "2026-02-16T07:22:16Z",
        "comment_author": "azure-pipelines",
        "comment_body": "<samp>\nAzure Pipelines successfully started running 1 pipeline(s).<br>\r\n\n</samp>"
    },
    {
        "number": 71,
        "repo": "sonic-ztp",
        "comment_at": "2026-02-16T07:22:46Z",
        "comment_author": "yxieca",
        "comment_body": "Good catch @Ryangwaite \u2014 fixed in 045ca9a. The shutdown log block now checks minigraph.xml first, matching the discovery order in `__discover()`. So when both files exist you should now see:\n\n```\nsonic-ztp: ZTP service started.\nsonic-ztp: minigraph.xml found, skipping ZTP discovery.\nsonic-ztp: Configuration file /etc/sonic/minigraph.xml detected. Shutting down ZTP service.\n```\r\n"
    },
